The paper deals with the problem of spacecraft pose estimation using monocular vision, which is a common problem in robotics and autonomous systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for pose estimation, which falls under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a novel Gauss-Newton algorithm for estimating the position, which falls under the category of optimization and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of non-cooperative rendezvous, which is a common problem in control systems (cs.SY).
